<TITLE> Ctg mayor appears in court on charges of embezzlement </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 26 (bdnews24.com) -- Chittagong City Corporation mayor ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury appeared before the Divisional Special Judges' Court for Chittagong Wednesday on charges of embezzlement involving private TV station 'Bijoy'. CCC chief executive officer Imtiaz Hossain Chowdhury also appeared in the court as co-accused in the case. Judge SM Solaiman set Jan 1 as the date for the next appearance of the accused before the court, as there had been no gazette notification published to date naming CCC chief engineer Mokhter Alam as another co-accused in the case. Zahirul Haque, who acted for the state, told bdnews24.com that the court deferred proceedings as there had been no gazette notification by Wednesday. If the gazette notification was not published by Jan 1, however, the court would nevertheless go ahead and set the hearing date for framing charges, Zahir added. Anticorruption Commission deputy director Abu Mohammad Aref Siddique filed the case with Kotwali police against the three for allegedly syphoning Tk 80 lakh from city corporation funds to run the private TV station. Investigation officer in the case, ACC assistant director Abul Kalam Azad, pressed the charges in court on Nov 22. The CCC mayor had earlier appeared before court on Dec 4. bdnew
